            <section class="topic_section">
                <div class="row topic_row">
                    <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">                   

                        <h2>$15 an Hour?</h2>

                        <p>Some Cambridge city councilors have discussed implementing a higher minimum wage in the city, but others question the effectiveness and legality of that proposal.</p>

                        <h5>Currently</h5>

                        <p>
                        <ul>
                        
                        <li>In June 2014, the city council passed an ordinance asking the city manager to look into the feasibility of increasing the minimum wage. (<a href="http://cambridge.wickedlocal.com/news/20160622/cambridge-task-force-formed-for-15-raising-minimum-wage-called-moral-move">Wicked Local Cambridge</a>)</li>
                        <li>Two years later, the council unanimously voted to establish a task force to explore the impacts of such a raise and recommend how to implement it without disrupting local businesses.(<a href="http://cambridge.wickedlocal.com/news/20160622/cambridge-task-force-formed-for-15-raising-minimum-wage-called-moral-move">Wicked Local Cambridge</a>)</li>
                        <li>Seattle passed a $15/hour minimum wage in 2014, which some say has reduced working hours and overall pay for vulnerable workers while others find that it increases wages. (a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/ronaldholden/2017/06/26/dueling-studies-come-to-opposite-conclusions-regarding-seattles-15-minimum-wage/#3f5a9bd393da">Forbes</a>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/26/business/economy/seattle-minimum-wage.html">NY Times</a>)</li>
                        <li>There are concerns that the city council doesn’t have the legal authority to pass an increase to minimum wage that raises it above the state minimum, which stands at $11/hour as of January 2017. (a href="https://www.bostonglobe.com/business/2015/12/02/why-aren-mass-cities-enacting-minimum-wage/3yhfXPPpEqUghnIYBvkIoK/story.html">Globe</a>)</li>
                        
                        </ul>
                        
                        </p>

                        <h5>In the Future</h5>

                        <p>
                        
                        <ul>
                        
                        <li>Is $15 minimum wage something Cambridge should move toward?</li>
                        <li>What impact would wage increases have on individuals? On businesses?</li>
                        
                        </ul>
                        
                        </p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

